comments.text:
Forza Horizon 5 -
5060 Ti using less than half the power. GPU is 20° cooler. Using less memory and less CPU resources. Pulling 15fps less, but maintaining a higher 0.1% low.

Red Dead Redemption 2 -
Same situation as Forza except it's a 10fps gap and not 15fps.

Silent Hill 2 -
5060 Ti using less than half the power and running more than 10° cooler. CPU running cooler. Memory usage is a bit heavier on the 5060 Ti. 1% lows, 0.1% lows, and avg FPS are neck and neck between both cards.

STALKER 2 -
Cards are neck and neck, but 5060 Ti is doing it at less than half the power consumption and is 12° to 15° cooler.

Cyberpunk 2077 - 
3080 is up an average of 8fps overall, but the 5060 Ti is using less than half the power, is 10° cooler, and using less memory. The CPU on the 5060 Ti system is also being utilized less and running cooler.

God of War Ragnarok - 
5060 Ti behind 10 to 15fps on average. Still using less than half the power and ~15° cooler. CPU usage and temps are pretty equal between both systems. 

Horizon Forbidden West -
Same situation. 3080 pulling maybe 10fps more, but using double the power and running 10°+ hotter than the 5060 Ti. CPU on the 5060 Ti system is actually using a good bit of power LESS and it's also cooler by an average of more than 5°C.

Kingdoms Come Deliverance 2 -
5060 Ti is running ~20°C cooler and using less than half the power of the 3080 (seeing the trend yet?). The 5060 Ti's CPU is running a few degrees cooler and using less power. 3080 system pulling an average of 9fps more.

Black Myth: Wukong -
Neck and neck in frame rates. 5060 Ti using less than half the power and is 10°C cooler. Interesting thing here is the 0.1% low. The 5060 Ti system is maintaining a ~23fps 0.1% low while the 3080 system is around 5fps.

The Last of Us Part II -
3080 less than 10fps advantage, using more than double the power, running 10°-15° hotter. 1% lows are neck and neck, but 0.1% lows favor the 5060 Ti again.

Overall --
3080 uses more than double the power at 10° to 20°C hotter temps to achieve MAYBE 10 more fps in these titles at max 1440p. Overclock the 5060 Ti even a little bit and it'll surpass the 3080 while STILL running colder at less power consumption. 

- Kindly, 
5090 Astral user 😘

comments.text: @bigturkey1  you are literally running the game at 1/4 that speed which is 45FPS.  That's exactly how it works and I'm not even including the held back frame which also slightly harms latency.  Compare 180 fps latency to 45.  22ms frame time vs 5.5ms frame time.  So you have that difference plus that one of those 22ms frames has to be held back adding additional delay.  The game itself normally has a 20-30 Ms delay before any of this is taken into account so that will be even for both experiences but the extra delay is very noticeable when you can only directly interact with 45 of those 180 frames and the rest are just estimations done by AI of what the in-between frames should look like.  I'm not even saying it's bad tech.  It's a great win more feature when games are already running well but the marketing behind it was garbage.
